The paper discusses the challenges of performing data cube analysis on large-scale data, which is a common problem in data warehousing and OLAP. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new system called HaCube that uses MapReduce and parallel DBMS to perform efficient parallel data cube analysis, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the data mining (cs.DM) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed) sub-categories.
